<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1351,1676]" box="[198,1229,1501,1527]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,361,1501,1527]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Distribution:</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[368,451,1501,1527]" name="France" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">France</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[463,517,1501,1527]" name="Italy" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Italy</collectingCountry>
and the Maghreb (
<bibRefCitation author="Bosmans, R." box="[738,918,1501,1527]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="117 - 163" refId="ref42573" refString="Bosmans, R. (2007) Contribution to the knowledge of the Linyphiidae of the Maghreb. Part XII. Miscellaneous Erigonine genera and additional records (Araneae: Linyphiidae: Erigoninae). Bulletin de la Societe Royal Belge d'Entomologie, 143, 117 - 163." type="journal article" year="2007">Bosmans 2007</bibRefCitation>
). First record for 
<collectingCountry box="[1122,1225,1501,1527]" name="Portugal" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Portugal</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1351,1676]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,366,1538,1564]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Habitat 
<typeStatus box="[302,360,1538,1564]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">type</typeStatus>
:
</emphasis>
Mostly collected in marshy areas, in fresh as well as in salt water marshes along the coast (
<bibRefCitation author="Bosmans, R." box="[159,339,1576,1602]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="117 - 163" refId="ref42573" refString="Bosmans, R. (2007) Contribution to the knowledge of the Linyphiidae of the Maghreb. Part XII. Miscellaneous Erigonine genera and additional records (Araneae: Linyphiidae: Erigoninae). Bulletin de la Societe Royal Belge d'Entomologie, 143, 117 - 163." type="journal article" year="2007">Bosmans 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1351,1676]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,338,1613,1639]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Phenology:</emphasis>
In the Maghreb, males were collected from December to April, females from January to August (
<bibRefCitation author="Bosmans, R." box="[251,430,1650,1676]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="117 - 163" refId="ref42573" refString="Bosmans, R. (2007) Contribution to the knowledge of the Linyphiidae of the Maghreb. Part XII. Miscellaneous Erigonine genera and additional records (Araneae: Linyphiidae: Erigoninae). Bulletin de la Societe Royal Belge d'Entomologie, 143, 117 - 163." type="journal article" year="2007">Bosmans 2007</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[482,584,1650,1676]" name="Portugal" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Portugal</collectingCountry>
, the species is expected to be adult in winter as well.
</paragraph>
